comment.narrative:
Baseline is established in 2013 (as per prodoc.)

1. Share of hural members that have received formal training (source: project M&E system); 
- No formal data;
- No formal training programme for hural members;
- No institutionalized training system, but ad hoc training by Academy of Management and MALA, more focused on legal environment and a set of core competencies not identified;
2. Increased hural capacity to fulfil their duties (see below in the Indicator section on sub-indicators); 
- No formal data;
3. Increased citizen participation; 
- None of hurals holding their meetings open to public;
- No data on number of public discussions held in Citizens' Halls;
- No data on adoption of hural resolutions that reflect concerns raised by citizens;
- 55% of the survey participants are not aware of about the role and functions of local hurals; 
- No legislative provision specifying public participation in hurals;
- Lack of internal procedures for engaging public in hural activities; 
4. Improved linkages between hural and administration (source: mid-term and end-project survey to be conducted amongst hural members, governors offices and citizens); 
- Number of issues arising in hural and administration relationships have not been formally identified;
5. Legal and policy lessons adopted (source: laws passed)
- Amendments to LATUG discussed mainly by and within hurals; 
- Lack of public discussion on amendments to LATUG;
- Lack of consensus on potential solutions to issues raised in relation to LATUG;

Scale 3. Law adopted and its implementation rolled out.

Actions to achieve the target:
1. Law on development policy and planning approved by the Parliament
2. Long-term development policy document is prepared;
3. Inclusive Green Economy aspects reflected in national  vision document, other policies and plans;
4. A position paper on linking natural resources management with HD is prepared;
5. T21 model expanded to population, labour, energy and housing sectors
6. new indicators and methodologies adopted and used in local planning
7. Data literacy strategy is in place  with action pkans;
8. Local center of excellence for data collection is established
9. NHDR on Youth is Launched
10. National Voluntary Presentation is prepared and presented to Annual Ministerial Meeting in NY;

description.narrative:
Indicator 1. Extent of progress made in operationalizing the ITT - LLDC. 
Indicator 2. Number of studies commissioned and used for policy debate.

The indicator 1 is measured by the scales from 0-2: 
Scale #0. ITT is not operational; 
Scale #1. ITT is established and with regular events organized on an annual basis; 
Scale #2. ITT is fully operational and the legal framework secured)
